ZH: 我看到血就会晕。
EN: I faint at the sight of blood.

ZH: 他看到惊人的牌子，差点晕了过去。
EN: He nearly passed out when he saw the shocking sign.

ZH: 坐高铁让我晕。
EN: Riding the high-speed train makes me dizzy.

ZH: 春季花粉过敏使她感到晕。
EN: Her pollen allergy makes her feel lightheaded in the spring.

ZH: 他从飞机上看到地面晕了。
EN: He felt dizzy looking down at the ground from the plane.

ZH: 待在车里会让他感到晕。
EN: Sitting in the car makes him feel dizzy.

ZH: 他把头从高处往下低，结果晕了。
EN: He lowered his head from a high place and felt dizzy.

ZH: 旋转木马总会让我晕。
EN: The carousel always makes me dizzy.

ZH: 轮船的摇晃会让我晕。
EN: The swaying of the boat makes me dizzy.

ZH: 高温天气会让人感到晕乎乎的。
EN: Hot weather can make people feel dizzy.

ZH: 乘坐过山车时，一些人会感到晕。
EN: Some people feel dizzy when riding a roller coaster.

ZH: 喝了那么多酒，他差点晕了。
EN: He almost fainted after drinking so much alcohol.

ZH: 不吃早餐会让你头晕。
EN: Skipping breakfast can make you feel lightheaded.

ZH: 长时间玩手机会让你晕。
EN: Playing on your phone for a long time can make you feel dizzy.

ZH: 在高山上呼吸稀薄的空气时，人容易感到晕。
EN: People can feel dizzy when breathing thin air on high mountains.

ZH: 听到这个坏消息，她当场晕倒。
EN: She fainted on the spot upon hearing the bad news.

ZH: 在高空看下去，让我晕。
EN: Looking down from a great height makes me feel dizzy.

ZH: 我的头痛得厉害，感觉快要晕了。
EN: My headache was so severe that I felt like passing out.

ZH: 过度劳累会让你感到头晕眼花。
EN: Overworking can make you feel dizzy and blurry-eyed.

ZH: 面对那么多考试压力，她感到头晕。
EN: Faced with so much exam pressure, she felt lightheaded.
